  "instructions": [
    "Heat sesame oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add sliced onions and cook until softened, about 8 minutes.",
    "Add grated ginger and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add sliced mushrooms and cook until they release their liquid and start to brown, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add bamboo shoots, duck meat, soy sauce, honey, rice vinegar, star anise, cinnamon stick, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Pour in water and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Cover the Dutch oven and transfer it to the oven. Cook for 25 minutes or until the meat is tender and the flavors have melded together.",
    "Remove the Dutch oven from the oven and let it cool slightly.",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve hot over steamed rice.",
    "Let the tagine rest for 10 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to redistribute."
  ],
